<h2>Payment & delivery</h2>

<p><strong>Pay on delivery.</strong> Venmo, Zelle, or cash, whatever's easiest. We text you the total the day before so there are no surprises.</p>

<p><strong>No subscription, no auto-charge.</strong> Order any week you want, skip any week you don't. We'll text you each week to confirm your standing order or to ask if you'd like something new.</p>

<p><strong>Free delivery</strong> within our service neighborhoods: Lake Mary, Sanford, Winter Springs, Oviedo, Casselberry, Maitland, Winter Park, College Park, and Downtown Orlando. <a href="/order/">See the full schedule and place an order →</a></p>

<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:50px"><a href="/assets/volkman-price-list.pdf">Download printable price sheet (PDF)</a></p>

<h2>Common questions about pricing</h2>

<details><summary>Is there a minimum order?</summary><p>One ounce per week is enough to start. Two to four ounces is what most households end up at after a few weeks.</p></details>

<details><summary>Is delivery free?</summary><p>Yes, free across all nine service neighborhoods. No tipping expected.</p></details>

<details><summary>How long do they last in the fridge?</summary><p>About 7 days from harvest, in their clamshell, in your crisper drawer. That is why we cut them the morning we deliver: you get the full week of freshness instead of the leftover days other people sold.</p></details>

<details><summary>Is the 10% standing-order discount the only price break?</summary><p>Yes for retail. Wholesale pricing for restaurants is volume-based and quoted separately on the <a href="/restaurants/">restaurants page</a>.</p></details>

<details><summary>Why is every variety the same price per ounce?</summary><p>We grow them all in the same trays in the same shed with the same care. Some take longer than others, some take more seed, but on the customer side it averages out and a single flat price is easier for everyone. No surprises at checkout.</p></details>

